abstract = "Background and aims
It is widely recognized that chronic hepatitis C is a metabolic disease that is strongly associated with type 2 diabetes mellitus (T2DM) and insulin resistance (IR). The evidence behind the effect of Direct Anti-Viral Agents (DAAs) therapy on T2DM is conflicting. The aim of the present study was to evaluate the effect of treatment with DAAs on glycemic control in patients with type-2 diabetes mellitus and chronic hepatitis C virus genotype 4.
