We measured serum DPP-4 level in 50 patients with T1DM recruited from the Diabetes Endocrine Metabolism Pediatric Unit, and in 80 healthy controls. IR was assessed by the equation for estimated glucose disposal rate (eGDR). Biochemical evaluation including glycated haemoglobin (HbA1C) and lipid profile were included.
Results
IR was found in 80% of patients with T1DM. DPP-4 was significantly higher in control group than patients with T1DM. Patients with T1DM were classified into 3 groups according to DPP-4 tertiles showing significant increase in BMI SDS and total cholesterol across the 3 groups. Significant correlation was found between DPP-4 levels and insulin dose. DPP-4 was significantly higher in patients with T1DM with good glycemic control.
