Eighteen hundred consecutive patients who underwent elective CABG were included. Following exclusion criteria, a total of 1017 subjects were included for final analysis. 692 (68%) patients had T2DM and 325 (32%) patients had no T2DM. Data were obtained by collecting clinical data, routine biochemistry and chest imaging. Patients were followed up to 7 days postoperatively.
