DPP4 activity was not different between the two groups (PM 5309 ± 650 vs PreM 5387 ± 704 RLU; p = 0,70). In the PM group there was a significant correlation between DPP4 and body weight (r = 0,498; p = 0,03; n = 22) and trunk fat (r = 0,477; p = 0,03; n = 21). There was also a trend for correlation with android (r = 0,418; p = 0,06; n = 21) and total fat (r = 0,409; p = 0,06; n = 21). When stratified by BMI, DPP4 was significantly higher in PM women with BMI ≥25 kg/m2 (p = 0,02).
