keywords = "Diabetes, Metabolic syndrome, Obesity, Atherogenic dyslipidemia, Handedness",
abstract = "Background
Type 2 diabetes (T2DM) is associated with obesity, insulin resistance and the metabolic syndrome (MetS). In non-diabetic populations, features of metabolic obesity (MO) are observed in a minority of normal-weight (NW) subjects. The cardiometabolic status of metabolically obese but normal-weight (MONW) individuals has not yet been phenotyped in T2DM.
