Results
Osteocalcin correlated negatively with fasting glucose (r=−0.366, p<0.001) and HOMA-IR (r=−0.305, p<0.05) but not with waist circumference (r=0.079), body mass index (r=0.028), total cholesterol (r=0.061) or triglycerides (r=0.009). Diabetics had higher HOMA-IR (p<0.01) and lower osteocalcin levels (p<0.01) than non-diabetics. Among diabetics, osteocalcin correlated with glucose only (r=−0.341, p=0.015). In non-diabetics, osteocalcin correlated with HOMA-IR (r=−0.359, p=0.023) via insulin (r=−0.402, p=0.010). Patients with impaired fasting glucose levels (5.6–6.9mmol/L) had the same HOMA-IR as diabetics (p=0.076) but not low osteocalcin (p=0.025).
